The paper proposes a method for collision-avoidance navigation using reinforcement learning and 2D laser scans. This involves robotics (cs.RO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The method also involves analyzing and predicting the impact of the robot's actions on surrounding pedestrians, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV) or systems and control (cs.SY).
